chennai.description: Maruti is known among people for its range of power packed economical vehicles, and one such model which has become really popular is the Maruti Baleno. If you’re looking at a stylish hatchback, which is classy as well, then Baleno would be the perfect fit for your next road trip. This car has a sporty look and the interiors are really spacious as well. This hatchback has a seating capacity of 4+1, and the ample amount of space here makes you relax comfortably on long road journeys. This is a car with pretty much everything you would want from a premium hatchback, and offers you great mileage too. If you’re planning to rent it out for a few days, then this is one of the best options.

When you are planning to go for a road trip on the hills of North India, there is nothing better than hiring an SUV. A Mahindra Scorpio serves you well if you love driving a powerful car, which gives you rear wheel drive that is suitable for the curvy mountain roads. With 6+1 seats, you can drive with your entire family. If you go by cab, you have to accommodate a driver as well, but you can occupy that driver's seat with a Car Rental. While sitting in a Scorpio, you get better visibility of the road, and an SUV is any day more stable than smaller cars. The car is also safer than a tiny hatchback. You can conveniently dump all your bags in the back seat and yet sit comfortably throughout the journey.

The Hyundai brand has been in India for a long time, and people are just not ready to let it go. You cannot have enough a car from Hyundai because of the peace of mind it brings with it. The Hyundai Creta is another name for reliability and comfort. This gorgeous looking compact SUV has almost every feature that comes in a regular SUV. The proportionately balanced interior of Creta makes it a comfortable car for long road trips. For driving a vehicle on the Indian roads, great pickup is crucial in a car, which is definitely there in Hyundai Creta. You can drive the car on all sorts of hills and terrains with ease and never feel tired. Whether you are there in the city or on the outskirts, whether you want it in the diesel or petrol variant, Hyundai Creta is sure to impress you.

This car is quite perfect for the extended Indian families, in which people can sit comfortably in the seven seats of the spacious cabin. The fuel-efficient engine of Ertiga gives impressive mileage, which is an essential factor on the congested Indian roads. Only a proficient driver knows the importance of small turning radius because it is crucial to turn around the car in traffic jams. Concerning safety, even the third row of Maruti Ertiga offers a three-point seatbetls, unlike the lap belts. The light tones of the cabin make it look lighter and brighter than other cars, and the steering-mounted controls give in many bonus points. This no-nonsense car is just perfect for a road trip, no matter where you want to go.

Maruti has never failed to deliver excellent fuel efficiency, which is the same with Ciaz as well. The cabin of the car is the most spacious one among all Maruti cars till date, and even tall people can sit comfortably in the seats because of the expansive legroom. Since the time Innova Crysta was launched in the Indian market, people have showered it with love. This seven-seater car is perfect for a family road trip. Imposing new front silhouettes, stunning diamond-cut alloy wheels, crafted leather seats, Innova's legendary capabilities is power punched in Toyota Crysta. Its exterior design spells dominance and the well-appointed interior is steeped in luxury and elegance. The car comes with a well-equipped cabin, a sturdy engine, feature-filled interior, seven airbags, and tremendous fuel efficiency. All these things are crucial for a long road trip so that you do not have to fret over petty things.The spacious 7-seater car rental with its unequalled space and plushness offers you unmatched safety, connectivity, refined power and an unrivalled driving experience.

The MG Astor's red cabin, fittingly called Sangria, is now available in the one-below-top Sharp trim of the SUV. Previously, you could pick up the red interior theme only in the top-spec Savvy trim. It carries a premium of Rs 10,000 over the Ivory/Black interior colour in the naturally aspirated petrol-powered Sharp variants, while there is no additional cost for the turbo-petrol variant. The Astor is MG's compact SUV rivalling stalwarts like the Maruti Suzuki Grand Vitara and Hyundai Creta.The MG Astor comes equipped with two powertrains: a 110PS/144Nm 1.5-litre naturally aspirated petrol, and a 140PS/220Nm 1.3-litre turbo-petrol unit. Transmission options include a 6-speed manual and an 8-speed CVT for the NA motor and a 6-speed automatic for the turbo-petrol unit. The Astor is 4323mm long, 1809mm wide, 1650mm tall, and has a 2585mm wheelbase.MG packs the Astor with segment-first autonomous driver aid kit, which includes forward collision warning, autonomous emergency braking, adaptive cruise control, lane-keeping assist, and high-beam assist. Other features include a 10.1-inch touchscreen infotainment system with Apple CarPlay and Android Auto and connected car tech, a 7-inch digital driver display, AI-driven features with voice command-based functions, a panoramic sunroof, a 6-way powered driver seat, and automatic climate control. Safety is taken care of with six airbags, ABS with EBD, ESP, brake assist, a 360-degree camera, traction control, hill hold/descent control, and disc brakes on all wheels.

A decade ago, taking a hatchback for a road trip was the only resort for everyone, but the times are changing now. People want to drive sturdy cars on the mountains, but buying an SUV is not an option for everyone. A grand SUV is too tricky to drive in the city traffic but is excellent for a road trip. Maneuvering a compact SUV like Renault Duster is even easier when you have to drive on the curvy mountain roads. The enormous storage in the Duster combined with clean interiors and sleek exteriors is just the thing you would want for an extended road trip. The impressive fuel mileage gives Renault Duster bonus points since you will save more money than you will spend on a chauffeur-driven car.

Amaze is the superhero car for Honda, and this sub-four meter car is everything you need for a convenient road trip. The tremendous amount of headspace and legroom give a lot of room to the passengers to relax. The ergonomically designed Honda Amaze lets you access every button and comfort feature while driving. It comes with features like touchscreen entertainment unit, automatic climate control, steering mounted controls, cruise control, audio controls, and a powerful AC. The boot space is undoubtedly helpful to store your luggage that does not disrupt your travel. The fuel efficiency of Honda Amaze is a bonus when you are on a long road trip. However, Honda has given attention to its passengers by offering a bottle and cup holder in the rear as well. With so many features in just one car, what else do you need to have an accomplished road trip?

The new BMW 5 Series was launched in March, but the 520d has only just arrived; its emissions of 129 g/km CO2, together with 57.6 mpg, are class-leading for a large executive saloon.Think back a few years and no-one would have thought that a car of this size would be able to achieve almost 60 mpg. The new 520d shows how successful BMW has been in revolutionising the efficiency of its cars – without any sacrifices in the driving experience.This is in large part due to BMW rolling out its EfficientDynamics technology on all of its models. The BMW 520d, which shares a new engine with the 320d EfficientDynamics , is the first 5 Series to come with Auto Start-Stop, which reduces the engine idle period when coming to a short stop. Brake Energy Regeneration, which recharges the vehicle’s battery during engine over-run, is part of the standard specification for all 5 Series saloons.

The Mahindra Thar has 2 Diesel Engine and 1 Petrol Engine on offer. The Diesel engine is 2184 cc and 1497 cc while the Petrol engine is 1997 cc . It is available with Automatic & Manual transmission.Depending upon the variant and fuel type the Thar has a mileage of 15.2 kmpl & Ground clearance of Thar is 226mm. The Thar is a 4 seater 4 cylinder car and has length of 3985mm, width of 1855mm and a wheelbase of 2450mm.

Latest Update: Mercedes has launched the 2021 E-Class facelift in India and you can read our launch report here.Mercedes-Benz E-Class Variants and Prices: The Mercedes-Benz E-Class is available in three variants: Expression, Exclusive and a new AMG Line. The first two can be had with a petrol or diesel engine whereas the last one can only be had with a diesel engine. They are priced between Rs 63.6 lakh and Rs 80.9 lakh (both ex-showroom India).Mercedes-Benz E-Class Engine and Transmission: The Expression and Exclusive variants of the E-Class can be had with a 2.0-litre petrol (E200) or diesel (E220d) engine. The petrol engine makes 197PS and 320Nm of torque and the diesel engine makes 194PS and 400Nm of torque. The AMG line variant is offered with a 3.0-litre inline-six-cylinder diesel engine that makes 286PS and 600Nm of torque. All three engines are mated to a 9-speed automatic transmission.Mercedes-Benz E-Class Features: The E-Class gets features like all LED lighting, a panoramic sunroof, air suspension (only for AMG Line), three-zone climate control, reclining rear seats, a 12.3-inch fully digital instrument cluster integrated with a touchscreen infotainment system of the same size, 64 colour ambient lighting, front and rear wireless charging pads, parking pilot with a 360-degree camera, and a 590W Burmester sound system. In terms of safety, there are 7 airbags onboard, an electronic stability program, attention assist, and active brake assist.

The luxury sedan can be had in three variants: Premium, Premium Plus and Technology.Engine and Transmission: It is powered by the same 2-litre turbo-petrol engine (making 190PS and 320Nm) as the Q2 SUV. This unit is paired with a seven-speed DCT (dual-clutch automatic) and drives all four wheels.Features: Features on board the Audi A4 include a 10.1-inch touchscreen infotainment system with Android Auto and Apple CarPlay, a digital driver’s display, three-zone climate control, a 19-speaker B&O sound system, powered front seats and a sunroof.Safety: Its safety kit includes eight airbags, ABS with EBD, electronic stability control (ESC), all-wheel disc brakes, hill hold assist and a rear-view camera.
